He started to limp in the direction the girl went. The vampires wouldn't take a ghoul again, not unless they had permission form her master. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dhampirlordofmallorea>Dhampir Lord of Mallorea</A> at: 7/9/03 8:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taylea>Taylea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#8B4513>(7/10/03 4:01 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://rose-needles.net/tayav.jpg width=134 height=190></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A twisted turn of events.</span><hr size=1> As Vania pulled Taylee away from the stranger and began walking, the blonde girl looked over her shoulder with an apologetic glance back towards him. Even though he'd said he was ok, he had looked pretty beat up and she hoped he'd take Vania's advice and find the medical station.<br>
<br>
Turning her face back to the front, Taylee noticed that they were exiting the city once again. And then Vania was pulling the curtain aside and pushing Taylee into the darkness. At first Taylee couldn't see anything accept the solid blackness that comes with a sudden change in the level of light, and then it was too late...she felt the impact as Vania kicked out, and smelled the sweet metallic scent she knew too well. Blood. The echo of running footsteps brought her head up, listening, but they were moving away, and it was then that she knew she was alone.<br>
<br>
Taylee turned back, hurrying towards the city. It was her only hope...she knew what was out there waiting in the dark. As she got closer she could hear the commotion of people. Someone was screaming. And as she raised the curtain, breathing a sigh of relief to be back in the light, suddenly everything went black. 'No,' she thought, 'not here.' They were coming....she knew it down to the very core of her being. 'Could I have brought this on,' she asked herself as the light clicked back on flooding the city once again.<br>
<br>
She turned horrified eyes on the scene presenting itself in front of her. The screams seemed distant like something muffled and unreal, as she watched the vampires burn. And where they had stood multiple bodies littered the ground.<br>
<br>
In shock Taylee crouched down, shaking. What was she going to do now.<br>
<br>
