Looking up at Cynthia questioningly a moment, he quickly trots after Vania and Taylea, smelling the apprehension on Vania. As she pushes past a curtain into a very dark room, he flutters his eye lids quickly, dowsing the glowing blue orbs briefly to help adjust to the deeper darkness. The scent of Death was on the air.<br>
<br>
The great wolf stunned sudden violence displayed before him, howls angrily! Vania falls quickly before he can do anything.  A blinding flash of light brings to view many vampires bursting into flame. Howling angrily into the room, he looks quickly about. Taking note of Cynthia standing next to him, he sighs a soft huff of relief quiets his menacing growl still burning in his throat.<br>
<br>
As Taylea speaks, he turns his massive head to her, obvious intelligence lurking behind his pale eyes. A sticcato bark pierces the air as she mentions rescue. A serious cast to his wolfen face shows his acceptance, and understanding. <br>
<br>
A look of curious contemplation quickly sweeps his face, uncertain how to communicate his intentions and desires at the moment. Another softer more drawn out <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>wuff</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> echos in the still air.<br>
